ANACT makingsyntheticandsemisynthetickratomillegal.
BeitEnactedbytheSenateandHouseofRepresentativesinGeneralCourtconvened:
1 1 New Subdivision; Synthetic Kratom Policy. Amend RSA 318-B by inserting after section 50
2 thefollowingnewsubdivision:
3 SyntheticKratomPolicy
4 318-B:51 Definitions. Inthissubdivision, "synthetickratom"or"semisynthetickratom"means:
5 I. An alkaloid or alkaloid derivative that has been created by chemical synthesis or
6 biosynthetic means, including fermentation, recombinant techniques, yeast derived, and enzymatic
7 techniques, rather than traditional food preparation techniques, such as heating or extracting that
8 syntheticallyaltersthecompositionofanykratomalkaloidorconstituent;or
9 II. An alkaloid or alkaloid derivative contained in kratom that has been exposed to
10 chemicals or processes that would confer a structural change in the alkaloids, resulting in material
11 thathasbeenchemicallyaltered.
12 318-B:52 Synthetic Kratom Limitations. No person or entity person shall prepare, distribute,
13 manufacture,sell,possess,oradvertisesyntheticorsemisynthetickratom.
14 2 NewParagraph; ControlledDrugAct; SchedulingbytheCommissioner. Amend RSA318-B:1-
15 abyinsertingafterparagraphVIIIthefollowingnewparagraph:
16 IX. Notwithstanding paragraph I, synthetic or semisynthetic kratom shall be classified as a
17 scheduleIIcontrolleddrug.
18 3 EffectiveDate. Thisactshalltakeeffectuponitspassage.

